This article is a presidential proclamation issued by Barack Obama on March 4, 2011, to commemorate the 150th anniversary of the inauguration of Abraham Lincoln. The proclamation highlights Lincoln's role in holding together a divided country and freeing millions from slavery. It emphasizes Lincoln's belief in the unity of the nation and his efforts to heal the wounds of the Civil War. The proclamation calls on Americans to honor Lincoln's memory and uphold the principles he championed.